    <result id="7a69ab9e-b56d-493f-a75e-f4172f415b31">
      <name>Jenkins &lt; 2.197 and &lt; 2.176.4 LTS Multiple Vulnerabilities - Linux</name>
      <modification_time>2026-01-26T07:28:06Z</modification_time>
      <comment />
      <creation_time>2026-01-26T07:28:06Z</creation_time>
      <host>127.0.0.1<asset asset_id="13a9ba38-ceca-44f2-8867-4601dc05d807" /><hostname>host1.example.com</hostname></host>
      <port>8080/tcp</port>
      <nvt oid="1.3.6.1.4.1.25623.1.0.114139">
        <type>nvt</type>
        <name>Jenkins &lt; 2.197 and &lt; 2.176.4 LTS Multiple Vulnerabilities - Linux</name>
        <family>Web application abuses</family>
        <cvss_base>5.4</cvss_base>
        <severities score="5.4">
          <severity type="cvss_base_v3">
            <origin>NVD</origin>
            <date>2023-02-23T01:54:00Z</date>
            <score>5.4</score>
            <value>CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N</value>
          </severity>
        </severities>
        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=Jenkins is prone to multiple vulnerabilities.|insight=Jenkins is prone to the following vulnerabilities:

  - The f:expandableTextBox form control interpreted its content as HTML when expanded, resulting in
  a stored XSS vulnerability exploitable by users with permission to define its contents, typically
  Job/Configure. (CVE-2019-10401)

  - The f:combobox form control interpreted its item labels as HTML, resulting in a stored XSS
  vulnerability exploitable by users with permission to define its contents. (CVE-2019-10402)

  - The SCM tag name on the tooltip for SCM tag actions was not being escaped, resulting in a stored
  XSS vulnerability exploitable by users able to control SCM tag names for these actions. (CVE-2019-10403)

  - The reason why a queue item is blocked in tooltips was not being escaped, resulting in a stored
  XSS vulnerability exploitable by users able to control parts of the reason a queue item is blocked,
  such as label expressions not matching any idle executors. (CVE-2019-10404)

  - The value of the 'Cookie' HTTP request header on the /whoAmI/ URL was being printed, allowing
  attackers exploiting another XSS vulnerability to obtain the HTTP session cookie despite it being
  marked as HttpOnly. (CVE-2019-10405)

  - The values set as Jenkins URL in the global configuration were not being restricted or filtered,
  resulting in a stored XSS vulnerability exploitable by attackers with Overall/Administer permission.
  (CVE-2019-10406)|affected=Jenkins LTS up to and including 2.176.3, Jenkins weekly up to and including 2.196.|impact=|solution=Update Jenkins weekly to version 2.197 or later / Jenkins LTS to
  version 2.176.4 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update Jenkins weekly to version 2.197 or later / Jenkins LTS to
  version 2.176.4 or later.</solution>
        <refs>
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2019-10401" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2019-10402" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2019-10403" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2019-10404" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2019-10405" />
          <ref type="cve" id="CVE-2019-10406" />
          <ref type="url" id="https://jenkins.io/security/advisory/2019-09-25/" />
        </refs>
      </nvt>
      <scan_nvt_version>2023-10-27T16:11:32Z</scan_nvt_version>
