        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.1/AV:P/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:N|summary=Eclipse Jetty is prone to a vulnerability in the session
  management.|insight=If an exception is thrown from the SessionListener#sessionDestroyed()
  method, then the session ID is not invalidated in the session ID manager. On deployments with
  clustered sessions and multiple contexts this can result in a session not being invalidated. This
  can result in an application used on a shared computer being left logged in.|affected=Eclipse Jetty version 9.4.40.v20210413 and prior, 10.x through
  10.0.2 and 11.x through 11.0.2.|impact=|solution=Update to version 9.4.41.v20210516, 10.0.3, 11.0.3 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 9.4.41.v20210516, 10.0.3, 11.0.3 or later.</solution>
